🔑 global Keyword Kya Hai? (The Logic)
Python mein jab tum function ke andar koi variable likhti ho, 
to Python samajhta hai ke ye sirf is function ka "Zati" (Private) maamla hai.
Lekin agar tum chahti ho ke function ke andar ki gayi tabdeeli poore program (Global) par asar dale,
to tumhein global ka keyword use karna parta hai.


global ek Keyword ha: Kyunke Python ko batana parta hai ke "Bahar jao aur us variable ko pakro."
Ye ek Order (Hukm) ha 


Local variable
local koi Keyword nahi hai: Kyunke Python by default (khud-ba-khud) function ke andar
har nayi cheez ko "Local" hi manti hai. 
Is liye usay alag se batane ke liye kisi keyword ki zaroorat nahi parti.